The Central Bank of Nigeria,CBN said Thursday that it has commenced “a robust and coordinated investigation in collaboration with the Nigerian Financial Intelligence Unit (NFIU) and related agencies to uncover the unscrupulous persons and FX dealers who are creating this panic,” in the market. According to the CBN, “the full weight of our rules and regulations will be meted out to them, including, but not limited to, being charged for economic sabotage. The apex bank disclosed this in a statement debunking rumours of devaluation of the Naira. The CBN statement is ostensibly targeted at checkmating the panic fueled by the speculation in the forex market. Read the full text of CBN statement below: Market Fundamentals Do Not Support Naira Devaluation at This Time The Central bank of Nigeria (CBN) wishes to note with displeasure, the rumours and speculative activities of unscrupulous players in the foreign exchange market, borne out of the impression that the CBN is on the verge of devaluing the Naira, and triggering panic in the FX Market.  These rumours are false, unwarranted and calculated to serve their dubious and selfish ends. We therefore wish to state as follows: